# Testing and Docker (`tc`)

## Commands (Windows PowerShell)

```powershell
.\scripts\tc.ps1 test
.\scripts\tc.ps1 artisan test --filter=ScheduleCalculatorTest
.\scripts\tc.ps1 artisan test tests/Feature/Scheduling/SchedulerClaimingTest.php
.\scripts\tc.ps1 npm --prefix frontend run test
.\scripts\tc.ps1 npm --prefix frontend run build
```

Linux/macOS: `./scripts/tc.sh` with the same verbs.

## Backend tests

- PHPUnit; DB is SQLite `:memory:` (`phpunit.xml`). App runtime uses MySQL — keep migrations/queries portable.
- Layout: `tests/Unit/{Execution,Scheduling,Secrets}/`, `tests/Feature/Phase0/`, `Phase1/`, `Scheduling/`, plus dashboard/maintenance. Helpers in `tests/Support/` (`FixedClock`, `ArrayDnsResolver`, …).
- Freeze time via `Clock`; inject test DNS/outbound doubles — do not hit real network in unit tests.

## Local verification

There is no GitHub Actions CI. Before pushing, run through Docker (`tc`):

```bash
./scripts/tc.sh test
./scripts/tc.sh npm --prefix frontend run test
./scripts/tc.sh npm --prefix frontend run build
```

Optional: set `TC_CI=1` to use `compose.ci.yaml` for a CI-like compose overlay.
